        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 11:49AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1148 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Felton to near Ranburne, and moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tallapoosa, Carrollton, Roopville, Eubank Lake, Bowdon Junction,
Villa Rica, Bowdon, Tyus, Mount Zion, Roosterville, Buchanan, Clem,
Abilene, Draketown, Felton, Temple, John Tanner State Park, Bremen,
Lowell, and Blackjack Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 PM EDT for
northwestern Georgia. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in
effect until 700 PM EDT for north central and west central Georgia.</instruction>
